"a.感激的 【英】 adj. 感激的(expressing gratitude; appreciative) 【考】 amenity : comfortable / honorarium : grateful(宜人表示舒服/酬金 表示感谢) 【记】 不要和上面的 grate(磨碎)相混；in grate（n.忘恩负义者） 【例】 I was grateful to the stranger for returning my lost wallet. adj. (因为获得的好处)感激的, 感谢的 = appreciative 【记】不要和上面的grate(磨碎)相混; ingrate(n 忘恩负义者) 【类】amenity: comfortable = honorarium: grateful宜人表示舒服 = 酬金表示感谢 【记】gratitude 感谢；great 说你很伟大就是感谢你 【相关】gratitude 感谢，gratification 满意，gratify 满足，gratulation，congratulation 祝贺，ingrate 忘恩的，ungrateful 不领情的 grateful (adj.)  1550s, ""pleasing to the mind,"" also ""full of gratitude,"" from obsolete adj. grate ""agreeable, thankful,"" from Latin gratus ""pleasing"" (see grace (n.)). ""A most unusual formation"" [Weekley]. Hard to think of another case where English uses -ful to make an adjective from an adjective. Related: Gratefully; gratefulness."
